00:54:28.370 --> 00:54:31.660
We had a binder about three or
four inches thick, and when we got

00:54:31.660 --> 00:54:35.890
down to 150, cutting
those last 50, 25,

00:54:35.890 --> 00:54:40.330
like you know incredibly painful.

00:54:40.330 --> 00:54:46.340
And then when you cast that net so
wide and you're working full time,

00:54:46.340 --> 00:54:47.980
you can only visit so many places.

00:54:47.980 --> 00:54:51.690
So, you go to the best
repositories that you know of.

00:54:51.690 --> 00:54:54.810
But, that's not to say that
you can't sometimes get lucky.

00:54:54.810 --> 00:54:57.370
I worked at the National
Archives and I worked

00:54:57.370 --> 00:55:00.180
with an incredible archivist there.

00:55:00.180 --> 00:55:04.230
The Black Panthers were
investigated in 1970

00:55:04.230 --> 00:55:07.790
in a Congressional investigation

00:55:07.790 --> 00:55:12.500
and so they published a big thick
document, book detailing everything

00:55:12.500 --> 00:55:15.330
and there are photographs
in there as evidence.

00:55:15.330 --> 00:55:19.250
And I got really curious, well
where are those photographs now

00:55:19.250 --> 00:55:21.230
from the Congressional hearings?

00:55:21.230 --> 00:55:24.040
And sure enough somebody
was able to turn them

00:55:24.040 --> 00:55:26.140
up at the National Archives.

00:55:26.140 --> 00:55:30.500
And there were photographs that
somebody had taken locally,

00:55:30.500 --> 00:55:34.060
documenting where the free
breakfast centers were,

00:55:34.060 --> 00:55:36.640
where the Panthers were located.

00:55:36.640 --> 00:55:40.030
There were some other thigs
related, evidence of a bombing

00:55:40.030 --> 00:55:42.160
or somebody's car or something.

00:55:42.160 --> 00:55:43.700
And then there were
press photographs

00:55:43.700 --> 00:55:48.020
that the investigation
got from the local press.

00:55:48.020 --> 00:55:51.690
And then used to identify
everybody in it.

00:55:51.690 --> 00:55:54.220
There were police mug shots.

00:55:54.220 --> 00:55:59.370
So, this archive was squirrelled
away somewhere and it wasn't

00:55:59.370 --> 00:56:02.750
that the actual prints from the
evidence that I was able to find,

00:56:02.750 --> 00:56:06.430 position:56%
it was actually able to get them
through the publication of the book.

00:56:06.430 --> 00:56:08.630
So, they were the book files.

00:56:08.630 --> 00:56:09.930
You know, which was just crazy

00:56:09.930 --> 00:56:11.910
and you would never
think to look that way.

00:56:11.910 --> 00:56:16.780
So, often times you
might start on a search

00:56:16.780 --> 00:56:19.450
and then you get lucky
finding it elsewhere.

00:56:19.450 --> 00:56:21.200
And if I had started out looking

00:56:21.200 --> 00:56:26.150
for the book publication
files, they'd never exist, so.

00:56:27.730 --> 00:56:29.670
Yeah, great.

